    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_15_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_15",
      "description": "Presenting a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six with individual throttle bodies and an 8,000 RPM redline. This example is mechanically robust, with the critical VANOS system serviced and the rear subframe reinforced for structural integrity. Power is delivered through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a factory M Variable Differential Lock. The suspension maintains its composure with refreshed bushings and Bilstein dampers, offering tactile feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina consistent with a well-loved enthusiast machine, the drivetrain remains tight and responsive. A turn-key performance icon ready for the canyons.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_14_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_14",
      "description": "Used car. Good condition. Regularly maintained. Clean title. Runs well. No mechanical issues.",
